{
  "prompt": "Cross-sectional technical illustration of a 3-speed electric bicycle rear hub motor with internal electronic shifting system. The motor is integrated into the hub shell (135mm width), with three planetary gear sets clearly visible for each gear stage. The electronic shifting mechanism (both automatic and manual) is shown with wiring leading to the left side (in the direction of travel). The outer casing supports a disc brake mount. High-efficiency motor windings, magnets, and sensors are labeled. The image is clean, realistic, and mechanically accurate, in the style of an engineering blueprint with minimal color and a white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D cross-sectional technical illustration of a three-speed internally geared electric bicycle hub motor with Korean labels. The image shows internal gears, a 13T sprocket, planetary gear sets, a six-bolt disc brake mount, and an electronic shifting mechanism. All original French labels are translated into Korean: '입력 스프로켓 13T', '13T 기어', '저단 (1단 기어)', '135mm 허브 너비', '전자식 변속 장치', and '고단 (3단 기어)'. High detail, gray metal parts with gold accents for the electronic shift mechanism.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution cross-sectional 3D illustration of a 5-speed internally geared electric bicycle hub motor. The image shows a 135mm hub shell, with five planetary gear stages, each highlighted in different colors. An integrated BLDC motor is wrapped around the hub, and an electronic shifting mechanism is positioned on the left side, with gold actuators and sensors. The output shaft is aligned with a 13T sprocket, and the assembly includes a disc brake mount. Labels are in Korean, showing gear stages, motor, controller, and brake system. The design balances compactness and technical clarity.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A revised cross-sectional diagram of a five-speed internal gear hub motor for an electric bicycle, labeled in Korean. The diagram clearly shows the 13T input sprocket, five color-coded gear stages, the electronic shift mechanism, and now includes the solenoid actuators (전자석) positioned to control the gear clutch system. The solenoids are highlighted in red and placed near the right-hand side, adjacent to each gear selector stage. The diagram is labeled: '5단 기어 내장 허브모터 단면도 (전자석 포함)'",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A labeled technical illustration of a solenoid control system for a gear shifting mechanism. The image includes a cross-sectional view of a solenoid (copper coil, iron core, return spring), a push-pull plunger connected to a gear selector rod, and a microcontroller with an electrical signal path to the solenoid. Include Korean labels for key parts such as 전자석, 철심, 복귀 스프링, 기어 선택봉, and 제어신호.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "name": "gear_shift_simulator",
  "type": "code/javascript",
  "content": "// 📈 간단한 5단 전자변속 허브모터 시뮬레이터 (HTML + JS)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ko">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>5단 전자변속 허브 시뮬레이터</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: sans-serif; padding: 2rem; text-align: center; }
    .gear { font-size: 5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .slider-box { margin: 1rem 0; }
    label { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    input[type=range] { width: 80%; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>🔄 5단 전자변속 허브 시뮬레이터</h1>

  <div class="slider-box">
    <label>속도 (km/h): <span id="speed-value">0</span></label>
    <input type="range" id="speed" min="0" max="50" step="1" value="0">
  </div>

  <div class="slider-box">
    <label>토크 (Nm): <span id="torque-value">0</span></label>
    <input type="range" id="torque" min="0" max="100" step="1" value="0">
  </div>

  <div class="gear">⚙️ 기어: <span id="gear">1</span>단</div>

  <script>
    const speedSlider = document.getElementById('speed');
    const torqueSlider = document.getElementById('torque');
    const gearDisplay = document.getElementById('gear');

    function updateGear() {
      const speed = parseInt(speedSlider.value);
      const torque = parseInt(torqueSlider.value);

      document.getElementById('speed-value').innerText = speed;
      document.getElementById('torque-value').innerText = torque;

      let gear = 1;

      if (speed < 10 && torque > 30) {
        gear = 1;
      } else if (speed >= 10 && speed < 18) {
        gear = 2;
      } else if (speed >= 18 && speed < 25) {
        gear = 3;
      } else if (speed >= 25 && speed < 35) {
        gear = 4;
      } else if (speed >= 35) {
        gear = 5;
      }

      // 예외 처리: 토크가 높으면 다운시프트
      if (torque > 60 && gear > 1) gear--;

      gearDisplay.innerText = gear;
    }

    speedSlider.addEventListener('input', updateGear);
    torqueSlider.addEventListener('input', updateGear);
  </script>
</body>
</html>"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 3D cutaway illustration of a hub motor with an internal 3-speed gearbox using sliding spur gears (parallel gear system). The gears are arranged axially inside the hub, and a solenoid-controlled clutch mechanism selects the gear by sliding the central shaft left or right. Include cross-sectional view showing the gear teeth meshing and a compact solenoid actuator on the side. Technical style, white background, labeled parts, mechanical rendering.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A highly detailed cross-sectional technical illustration of a 5-speed internal gear hub motor system designed for electric bicycles. The structure combines a planetary gear (epicyclic) system with a sliding ring clutch mechanism for gear selection. The motor is integrated concentrically within the hub. The image should clearly show the sun gear, planet gears, ring gears, and sliding clutch components. Label the components in Korean, such as 중심축 (central axle), 유성기어 (planetary gear), 링기어 (ring gear), 슬라이딩 클러치 (sliding clutch), 전자석 (electromagnet), 모터 코일 (motor coil). Use a transparent, educational style as if for a mechanical engineering textbook.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 3D-rendered cross-sectional illustration of a 5-speed internal gear hub motor for an electric bicycle. The design features a planetary gear system (sun gear, planet gears, and ring gear), combined with a sliding clutch mechanism to switch between five gear ratios. The image should clearly show the gear stages, the solenoid-controlled sliding clutch mechanism, and the electrical motor windings around the hub. Annotations in Korean indicate each component, including '유성기어', '슬라이딩 클러치', '솔레노이드', '전기모터 권선', and '기어 단계'. Technical illustration style with a realistic and informative engineering aesthetic.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A highly detailed 3D-rendered cross-sectional diagram of a hub motor with a 5-speed internal gear system using planetary gears (epicyclic gears) and a sliding clutch mechanism. The image should show: 1) the central motor rotor, 2) stator coils, 3) three-stage planetary gear sets arranged in series, 4) a sliding clutch ring with solenoid actuators, 5) the outer hub casing connected to the bike wheel, 6) cross-sectioned annotations for gear ratios and shift engagement points. The illustration should resemble a technical schematic with clear labeling, metallic textures, and semi-transparent overlays to reveal internal components.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical cross-sectional illustration of a multi-stage planetary gear system integrated into a hub motor. The diagram shows an input shaft (yellow) feeding power into a series of layered planetary gear sets (black), with each gear set arranged in a triangular formation from left to right. Red vertical lines represent shiftable clutch paths between gear stages. The entire structure is enclosed in a blue casing, and the output shaft (green) exits on the right side. The setup is optimized for an electric bicycle hub motor application.",
  "size": "1024x512"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed technical schematic of a multi-stage planetary gear system inside a hub motor for electric bicycles. The image shows an input shaft on the left connected to multiple planetary gear sets arranged in a sequence. Each planetary gear set includes a sun gear, planet gears, and a ring gear, clearly illustrated. The gear stages are aligned in series and controlled by a sliding clutch mechanism for gear shifting. The motor is integrated into the same housing and connected to the gear system. The output shaft is on the right. Color-coded components: yellow input, black gears, red clutches, green output, blue motor housing. Cross-sectional side view, clean digital illustration.",
  "size": "1024x512"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed 3D cross-sectional technical illustration of a bicycle hub motor with a novel internal gear system. The system features a series of stacked conical sun gears (like an external 7-speed cassette), each aligned with matching planetary gear sets. Only one sun gear at a time connects to the input shaft via a sliding selector or solenoid-based clutch mechanism. The planetary gear sets orbit a common ring gear, and the output is transmitted through a shared carrier to the wheel axle. The image should be color-coded and labeled to distinguish sun gears, planetary gears, ring gear, clutch selector, input motor shaft, and output shaft. High-detail, mechanical engineering style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A corrected 3D cross-sectional digital illustration of a multi-stage planetary gear system for an electric bicycle hub motor. The illustration should show a conical set of sun gears (like an external 7-speed cassette) aligned along the axis. Each sun gear corresponds to its own matching set of planetary gears positioned correctly around it. The planet gears mesh with a shared ring gear fixed to the hub shell. A selector mechanism (solenoid or sliding selector) allows only one sun gear to engage with the input shaft at a time. The input shaft is inline (centered) to allow motor torque transfer, not from a chain, but from a direct motor drive system (such as a coaxial motor core). The output is connected to a central carrier that delivers torque to the bicycle wheel. The entire system is enclosed within a hub motor casing. Cutaway view must be technically accurate, clean, and detailed.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed technical cross-sectional 3D illustration of a bicycle hub motor featuring a conical multi-stage sun gear system. The image shows 5 layered sun gears stacked in a cone-like shape, each connected to a matching set of planet gears surrounding them. Each sun gear contains an internal ratchet mechanism. The ratchets allow torque to be transmitted selectively: the lower gears engage first, and upper gears can engage additionally without disengaging the lower ones. The structure is enclosed in a hub casing, and the input shaft is integrated with an electric motor. The output is transmitted through a central carrier or ring gear. Clean, precise mechanical labeling and clarity of gear relationships are shown.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A corrected 2D technical cross-sectional diagram of a multi-stage internal gear hub for an electric bicycle. The diagram shows a cone-shaped arrangement of multiple sun gears (like a bicycle cassette, nested concentrically), each corresponding to a matched set of planetary gears. Each sun gear has an internal ratchet mechanism. The planetary gears surround each sun gear accordingly, all inside a hub casing. Only one sun gear at a time engages via an internal clutch or solenoid selector. Power flows from left to right: the motor drives the selected sun gear, which transmits torque through the matched planetary set to a fixed ring gear and then to the output shaft. Lower gear ratchets remain engaged even if upper gear ratchets are also engaged. All components are shown in correct spatial arrangement, inspired by a Shimano-style internal gear hub. Technical style, line-based, clean cross-section.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A corrected 3D cross-sectional technical illustration of a bicycle hub motor with internal planetary gears. The hub maintains a cylindrical outer shell suitable for spoke mounting. Inside, multiple conical sun gears are aligned on a common axis, each corresponding to a planetary gear ring. Each sun gear includes an internal ratchet mechanism allowing torque transmission only when engaged. The output is connected to the common carrier or ring gear. Emphasis is placed on realistic geometry allowing spoke assembly on both sides of the hub. The structure avoids tapering inward and respects practical bike hub proportions.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed, labeled 3D-style technical cross-sectional illustration of an internal multi-speed bicycle hub system. The design shows multiple stepped sun gears (conical stack, like a sprocket set) mounted on a central shaft. Each sun gear corresponds to a ring gear fixed inside the hub shell (rotating outer housing). A ratchet mechanism is embedded in the shaft, allowing selective engagement of one or more sun gears. Non-engaged gears rotate freely without transmitting torque. The outer ring gears are press-fit inside the rotating hub shell. One or more sun gears may be ratcheted (locked), transmitting torque directly to the matching ring gear. The remaining gears co-rotate freely. The system is designed for immediate power transfer during downshifts (lower gears remain locked). Include labels: Shaft, Sun Gears, Ratchet Lock, Ring Gears, Hub Shell (Rotating), Torque Path.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A corrected 2D cross-sectional technical diagram of a bicycle hub motor internal gear system. The shaft passes through the center horizontally. Multiple sun gears are stacked in a stepped, conical formation at the center, each connected to the shaft via individual ratchets. These ratchets are precisely located where the shaft meets each sun gear. Surrounding the sun gears are multiple ring gears, also arranged in a stepped fashion that mirrors the sun gears' conical shape inversely. The ring gears are fixed inside the hub's outer shell, which represents the rotating part of the wheel. The diagram clearly shows the layered gear structure with labels: '샤프트', '다단 선기어', '다단 링기어', and '회전체'. The background is clean, white, and highly technical in style.",
  "referenced_image_ids": ["232a6462-8e40-45ec-9307-f39eb0050059"]
}

{
  "prompt": "A precise technical cross-sectional diagram of a novel internal gear hub system for an electric bicycle. The design features a conical multi-step sun gear on an input shaft (colored purple), with each gear step corresponding to an opposing ring gear (colored red) embedded into the rotating outer hub shell (colored blue). Each sun gear has a ratchet locking mechanism connected to the input shaft. The output is through the rotation of the outer shell. Only one sun gear at a time engages to transmit torque, while others spin freely without engagement. The image is labeled, clearly showing the separated input and output shafts, ratchet locks, ring gears, and hub casing. Background is neutral gray, engineering diagram style, clear and schematic.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A detailed, labeled technical 3D-style cross-sectional diagram of a multi-stage bicycle hub gear system with no planet gears. The system uses a conical stack of sun gears attached to an input shaft, each corresponding to a ring gear embedded in the outer rotating hub shell. Show a ratchet-lock mechanism located at the input shaft, allowing selective engagement of one sun gear at a time. Indicate that non-engaged gears freewheel along. Highlight input shaft, output rotating hub shell, conical sun gear set, multi-ring gears, and internal ratchet lock. The style should be digital engineering illustration.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical GIF-style animation of a cross-sectional hub gear mechanism designed for an electric bicycle. The system shows a multi-step (conical) sun gear stack on an input shaft (purple), with a ratchet-lock mechanism controlling which sun gear engages. Each sun gear meshes with a corresponding ring gear embedded into the rotating hub shell (blue). The animation should show the input shaft rotating continuously while only the selected sun gear engages with its ring gear, turning the output hub. The other sun gears rotate freely without transmitting torque. When the ratchet lock shifts to a different sun gear, that gear engages and the torque transfer moves to the corresponding ring gear. Include clear, smooth transitions between gear selections and make the mechanical parts visibly interlocked and rotating.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical GIF-style animation (as a single frame) showing a cutaway view of a conical multi-step sun gear and multi-ring gear hub system. The central shaft rotates a selected sun gear which transfers torque to a matching ring gear embedded inside a rotating outer hub shell. The shaft includes a ratchet lock mechanism that engages only one sun gear at a time. The rest of the gears spin freely. The cutaway view clearly labels: input shaft, ratchet lock, sun gears (stacked in steps), corresponding ring gears, and rotating hub shell. Style is engineering drawing with clean color-coded parts (shaft - purple, sun gear - black, ring gear - red, hub shell - blue), with arrows indicating motion direction.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A precise cross-sectional technical illustration of a multistage internal gear hub system designed for an electric bicycle. The image shows a conical stack of multiple sun gears (black), each aligned along a central input shaft (purple), and a corresponding reverse conical arrangement of ring gears (red) embedded inside the outer hub shell (blue). The hub shell is the rotating part connected to the bicycle wheel via spokes. The sun gears are coupled with ratchet mechanisms to the shaft, allowing only the selected gear to transmit torque, while other gears rotate freely without power transfer. The image should reflect physical realism in gear alignment, tooth engagement angles, and proper torque flow from the selected sun gear through its ring gear to the rotating hub shell. Use clear labels: Input Shaft, Sun Gears, Ratchet Lock, Ring Gears, Rotating Shell. Emphasize mechanical feasibility and realistic geometry.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
